evidence.evidence_text: The unemployment rate in Costa Rica fell to 6.3% in the fourth quarter of 2025, down from 6.9% in the same period a year earlier.
Meanwhile, the employment rate edged down to 51.1% from 52.8%, as the number of employed individuals decreased by 47.9 thousand to 2.18 million.
At the same time, the labor force participation rate declined to 54.5%, down from 56.7%.
